    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="7"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Conference W And PW/1–1245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-12T18:00:00-06:00"
                            >January 12, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Department’s circular of January 11, 7 p.m. The Honduran Government has
                    accepted the Mexican invitation to the conference. Honduras is in substantial
                    agreement with the agenda as suggested by Padilla but changes item IV to include
                    “other affairs of general and immediate interest to the participating
                    governments” and adds a fifth item suggesting consideration of the resolution
                    adopted on January 8 by the Governing Board of the Pan American Union relative
                    to the request of the Argentine Government.</p>
                <p>Copies of the Padilla invitation and the Honduran reply are being transmitted
                    tomorrow by air mail despatch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Erwin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
